==English==
===Alternative spellings===
''nocht (Scottish); nowt''

===Etymology===
From Old English ''nōwiht''

===Noun===
'''nought'''
#a [[nothing]]; something which does not exist
#a thing or person of no worth or value; [[nil]]
#not any quantity of number; [[zero]]; the score of no points in a game
#the figure or character presenting zero

[[category:English nouns]]

===Adjective===
'''nought'''
#good for nothing; [[worthless]]
#[[wicked]], [[immoral]]
#zero

[[category:English adjectives]]

===Verb===
'''nought'''
#[[disregard]]; [[despise]]
#[[efface]] (oneself)

[[category:English verbs]]

===Adverb===
'''nought'''
#to no [[extent]]; in no way; [[not at all]]
#[[not]]

[[category:English adverbs]]

===Pronoun===
'''nought'''
#nothing; zero

